OL,3,CNightclubs to close in Portsmouth and
OL,4,CWindsor as chain enters administration
OL,6,FThree of the South East's biggest
OL,7,Fnightclubs have been closed with
OL,8,Fimmediate effect, after their owner,
OL,9,FRekom UK entered administration.
OL,11,FATIK Windsor, ATIK Dartford and PRYZM
OL,12,FPortsmouth, which employed hundreds of
OL,13,Fstaff between them, after a buyer for
OL,14,Fthe sites could not be found.
OL,16,FThey are among 17 sites across the
OL,17,Fcountry that have been closed, which
OL,18,FRekom UK said was down to an
OL,19,F"extremely difficult period" for the
OL,20,Flate-night sector.
